3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates funding rates every hour using the premium/discount between the perpetual contract price and the underlying TAO spot price. The 8-hour TWAP mechanism smooths funding rate volatility while maintaining market efficiency. Funding payments occur automatically between long and short positions based on the rate direction and magnitude. Cross-margin functionality allows traders to optimize capital efficiency across multiple positions when executing funding rate strategies."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TAO","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TAO perpetuals exhibit significant funding rate volatility due to the AI sector's speculative nature and Bittensor's unique subnet economics. The token's mid-tier trading volume creates opportunities for sustained positive or negative funding periods. RabbitX's zero gas fee structure makes frequent position adjustments economically viable for funding rate arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TAO funding rates on RabbitX have shown extreme volatility during AI sector rallies, with rates exceeding 100% annually during peak speculation phases. The token typically experiences prolonged positive funding periods during subnet expansion announcements or major AI developments. Negative funding rates often occur during broader market corrections, when leveraged longs are liquidated and shorts dominate positioning. The hourly settlement frequency on RabbitX allows for more granular capture of these rate fluctuations compared to 8-hour settlement exchanges."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange funding rate arbitrage between RabbitX and centralized exchanges like Binance or OKX can be profitable when rate differentials exceed transaction costs. RabbitX's zero trading fees provide an edge for high-frequency funding strategies, though the DEX's smaller liquidity pool may limit position sizes. Delta-neutral strategies work well during periods of high funding rate volatility, allowing traders to collect funding payments while minimizing directional price exposure. The Starknet infrastructure enables rapid position adjustments needed for optimal funding rate capture."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's early-stage protocol status presents smart contract risks that traders must factor into funding rate strategies. The exchange's limited liquidity compared to major CEXs can cause slippage during large position entries or exits, eroding funding rate profits. TAO's inherent volatility can trigger unexpected liquidations even in delta-neutral setups if position sizing is inadequate. Traders should monitor the exchange's total value locked and daily volumes, as low liquidity periods can make funding rate arbitrage strategies temporarily unprofitable."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are TAO funding rates calculated on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX calculates and settles TAO/USDT funding rates every hour, providing more frequent opportunities to capture rate changes compared to exchanges with 8-hour cycles. The rates are determined by the price premium/discount between the perpetual and spot markets."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for TAO perpetuals on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for TAO/USDT perpetual futures. However, there are no gas fees for trading due to the off-chain matching engine, making frequent position adjustments cost-effective for funding rate strategies."},{"question":"Can I use cross-margin for TAO funding rate arbitrage on RabbitX?","answer":"Yes, RabbitX supports cross-margin trading, allowing you to use collateral across multiple positions. This is particularly useful for delta-neutral funding rate strategies where you might hold offsetting positions in TAO and other assets."},{"question":"What risks should I consider when trading TAO perpetuals on RabbitX?","answer":"Key risks include RabbitX's early-stage protocol status, limited liquidity compared to major exchanges, and TAO's high volatility. Smart contract risks are present, and low liquidity can cause slippage that may offset funding rate gains."}]}]
